Program: Outlook
Title: Torn Between Two Countries
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01gsjfk
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 24 Sep 2013
Majid Rafizadeh talks about the challenges he has faced because of his dual identity as a Syrian-Iranian. Also on the programme, neuro-scientist and musician Dave Soldier explains how he created an elephant orchestra at a Thai conservation centre. And, on the subject of music listen to Nicholas McCarthy, the first one-armed pianist to ever graduate from the Royal College of Music in London, plus a report from an international contortion convention in Germany. Show less